\section*{Reflection principle}

\begin{itemize}
\item Draw picture of two paths that reflect at $M$
\item  1/2 of all paths that reach $M$ end up above $M$ at the end
\item The other half endup below $M$.
\item Hence $P(\max_{i=1,n} X_i > M) = 2 P( X_n > M)$
\item But this is easy to compute!  Just a Binomial.
\item We can even use the CLT to get a handle on the probabilities.
\end{itemize}

