\section*{Return times to zero: proof using reflection principle}

\begin{itemize}
\item First step is say down
\item What is the probability of the max ever going above one and
ending at exactly zero?
\item Look for reflected paths.  Every path that does above one can be
split into two--one that ends at zero and one that ends at two.
\item THese are the probabilities we are after
\end{itemize}

